metadata.title: Diamond DA42 Twin Star
aws::graph::propositions: Military Operators of Diamond DA42 Twin Star
Argentine Army operates 3 DA42M surveillance aircraft.
Ghana Air Force operates 2 DA42M surveillance aircraft.
Ghana Air Force operates 1 DA42 training aircraft.
Jamaica Defence Force operates Diamond DA42 Twin Star aircraft.
Niger Air Force operates 2 DA42M surveillance aircraft.
Polish Air Force operates 5 DA42 aircraft.
Federal Security Service of Russia ordered 2 DA42M-NGs fitted with reconnaissance equipment in May 2016.
The DA42M-NGs ordered by Federal Security Service of Russia were due for delivery by November 2017.
Russian Ministry of Defence ordered 35 DA42Ts.
The first 3 DA42T aircraft were delivered to Russian Ministry of Defence in 2017.
An unknown number of DA42T aircraft were delivered to Russian Ministry of Defence in 2018.
Russian Ministry of Defence ordered 20 more DA42T aircraft in August 2020.
Eritrean Air Force operates 4 DA42Ts used for training.
Rwandan Air Force operates 2 DA42 aircraft used for transport.

text:
### Military operators

 Argentina
Argentine Army  3 DA42M surveillance aircraft.
 Ghana
Ghana Air Force   2 DA42M surveillance aircraft and 1 DA42 training aircraft
 Jamaica
Jamaica Defence Force
 Niger
Niger Air Force  2 DA42M surveillance aircraft
 Poland
Polish Air Force  5 DA42
 Russia
Federal Security Service (FSB)  2 DA42M-NGs fitted with reconnaissance equipment ordered in May 2016, with delivery due by November 2017.
Ministry of Defence  35 DA42Ts on order. First 3 aircraft delivered in 2017. Unknown number delivered in 2018. 20 more ordered in August 2020.
 Rwanda

Eritrean airforce 4 DA42 Ts used for training craft

Rwandan Air Force - 2 x DA42 used for transport.
